bowled him! Pathan is ecstatic. Vettori looks to pull this one from the leg-and-middle line, but it is not short enough. DV misses, YKP hits

No. 3 for YKP. He is over the moon. Mills goes for the big shot this time, the slog sweep, and Yusuf keeps firing them in. Mills misses, the ball hits the thigh pad outside the leg line, and then ricochets onto the stumps
big, big wicket! McCullum was looking very good here. He tried to go over short midwicket here, but got too close to this full delivery, thus not getting enough elevation. Ashwin is jubilant

plumb lbw first ball! A nothing shot really! Moves too far across, and also seems to have told himself to not play the forceful shot first ball. And the bat face closes too early, missing the ball, and he is caught dead in plumb. Tame end to what was shaping up to be an important innings of struggle followed by flourish

commentTextItems.html: and Tiwary finishes this off with a six to long-on and walks into a hug with Pathan

commentPostTextItems.html: With those endearing Yusuf quotes, we come to the end of the coverage for this exhilarating match. Thanks for joining us. Cheers
Presentation Anil Kumble is on the presentation party. Nice to see

Yusuf Pathan is the MoM He says, "This is very special for me. Whenever I have played any good innings, they have been something special. We were talking we need to take the game till the end. We needed some runs because we were behind on D/L, but the ball came on well. When me and Rohit were playing, we were saying once of us has to stay till the end of the 50th over. This innings could be the turning point for my life and my career" As it turned out, the game didn't even go into the 50th over. good on ya, Yousuf

Gautam Gambhir "I have never seen something like this. I have always said Yusuf can finish games on his own, and that's what he did today. I always felt till the time Yusuf was there we would win the game." [Yusuf can't stop smiling as Gautam praises him]. Nice moment there

Daniel Vettori "It's a great game of cricket. We were in the game, but Yusuf Pathan was pretty amazing. James played exceptionally well too to give us a formidable total, but like I said Yusuf took the game away. That break should have favoured us actually, but it didn't work out that way. The outfield wasn't that bad after that rain. We just didn't get it right."

And Pathan has single-handedly stolen this from New Zealand, who will be wondering what they need to do to win a damn game. They last won on August 10 in Dambulla. India, meanwhile, keep their unbeaten home season intact.

Pathan clinches his fist as he walks off. What an innings he played. More than the monstrous sixes he hit, his response to the short balls will stand out. He patiently ducked under them, not doing anything silly, but punished New Zealand every time they pitched it on a length. Spare a thought, too, for Franklin, who - like Pathan - got himself his personal best today

commentTextItems.html: and he is not tempted to finish it with a six, draws the scores level with a bunted single into the off side. Clenches the fist as he finishes the single
full and flat, pushed to long-off for one
full ball, on the pads, hit to midwicket
Pathan pushes this into the covers for one
slower ball, driven past mid-off, strong hit again, and India are one hit away now. What a turnaround

commentTextItems.html: short ball, Tiwary swings and misses
and Tiwary's brute power is now finding placement, driving - nay bludgeoning - this length delivery for four between the bowler and long-on
drives this to long-on for one

into the second tier! This man is hitting them brutally. He has missed the yorker by inches, and the low full toss is flying over long-on. And it just looks like a shovel shot in the replay, but how far has it travelled?
bouncer, Pathan ducks under it, called one for the over
advances down again, but ends up yorking himself

flat delivery, swatted powerfully to long-on for one
yorks him up, Pathan can't do much and squeezes it back
slog attempted, gets a thick inside edge that gets him a couple. He is squatting after every run he runs. Still looks strong
comes down the track to take this one the full and muscle it to wide long-on for one
good yorker, he keeps it out and takes a single to extra cover

dismissalComment.html: big, big wicket! McCullum was looking very good here. He tried to go over short midwicket here, but got too close to this full delivery, thus not getting enough elevation. Ashwin is jubilant

dismissalText.commentary: Scott Styris c Tiwary b Pathan 46 (48b 3x4 1x6 64m) SR: 95.83

dismissalComment.html: he is gone! Goes for the same chip over midwicket, but the ball is a bit too straight, and is also turning in, which makes him drag it a bit squarer than he wants and he finds Tiwary on the boundary

dismissalText.commentary: Ross Taylor lbw b Ashwin 44 (73b 3x4 0x6 112m) SR: 60.27

dismissalComment.html: plumb lbw first ball! A nothing shot really! Moves too far across, and also seems to have told himself to not play the forceful shot first ball. And the bat face closes too early, missing the ball, and he is caught dead in plumb. Tame end to what was shaping up to be an important innings of struggle followed by flourish

headshotImage.caption: Yusuf Pathan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Yusuf Pathan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Daniel Vettori b Pathan 17 (19b 2x4 0x6 24m) SR: 89.47

dismissalComment.html: bowled him! Pathan is ecstatic. Vettori looks to pull this one from the leg-and-middle line, but it is not short enough. DV misses, YKP hits

headshotImage.caption: Yusuf Pathan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Yusuf Pathan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Kyle Mills b Pathan 1 (6b 0x4 0x6 6m) SR: 16.66

dismissalComment.html: No. 3 for YKP. He is over the moon. Mills goes for the big shot this time, the slog sweep, and Yusuf keeps firing them in. Mills misses, the ball hits the thigh pad outside the leg line, and then ricochets onto the stumps

headshotImage.longCaption: Andy McKay player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Gautam Gambhir c Guptill b McKay 27 (24b 4x4 0x6 41m) SR: 112.5

dismissalComment.html: and what a way to get out after a missed run-out, an edge through slips! It was short, wide, juicy, and Gambhir has cut it straight to Guptill at point. Throat high. taken. Gambhir can't believe it

dismissalText.long: c sub (KS Williamson) b NL McCullum
dismissalText.commentary: Parthiv Patel c sub (KS Williamson) b NL McCullum 53 (57b 8x4 0x6 87m) SR: 92.98

dismissalComment.html: NMac is on fire here. Slows this one up, Patel comes down the track and goes for the big straight hit. Not quite close enough to the pitch of the ball and ends up skying it to long-on where substitute Williamson completes a tumbling catch

headshotImage.caption: Andy McKay player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Andy McKay player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Virat Kohli c Mills b McKay 0 (2b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: McKay has two! Kohli is gone for a duck after having scored 50 or more in his four previous innings. McKay's energy shows as he bowls another bouncer, angled across Kohli, who goes for the hook, gets a chunky top edge to Mills at long leg. New Zealand are right back

headshotImage.caption: Jamie How player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jamie How player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Yuvraj Singh c How b NL McCullum 20 (28b 1x4 1x6 38m) SR: 71.42

dismissalComment.html: and just when he started looking good, Yuvraj is gone! Goes for the pull again to a ball that is not quite short, gets zero elevation and finds short midwicket

dismissalText.commentary: Rohit Sharma c Vettori b Southee 44 (48b 4x4 1x6 56m) SR: 91.66

dismissalComment.html: the crowd is stunned into silence! Slower ball, Sharma saw it early, and looked to go over mid-off, but ended up smashing it straight down his throat. Vettori did well to hold onto it because it was hit very hard at it. Just couldn't get the elevation there
